post_text: Does your child receive free or reduced-price school meals during the school year, or do you believe you may now qualify based on a recent income change? Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not currently receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT today: https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt

post_text: Primero is tentatively planning on running a summer school program from June 1 through 26 from 8:30 AM until 12:30 PM. Classes will be Monday through Thursday for a total of 16 school days. We will operate within total compliance of the guidelines provided to us by the State of Colorado, CDE, and Las Animas County Health Department. Bus transportation will not be available due to social distancing concerns. Parents must drive their children to and from school daily. Students will be held in individual classrooms of 5 students per teacher--maximum. Space may be limited, so firm responses are necessary for participation. Primero will attempt to continue operating the Summer Food Service Program for the duration of summer school. The focus of summer school programming this year will be core instruction in Math, English (Reading and Writing) and support content designed to arrest the loss of learning experienced through remote instruction. Emails of serious interest only should go to bbyall@primeroschool.com.

post_text: Hello. Beginning Wednesday April 8 Primero will begin using the following revised schedule. On Monday and Wednesday students will log in to first, third, fifth and seventh hour. On Tuesday and Thursday they will log in to second, fourth and sixth hour. Please follow the same times as the two hour delay schedule. There will be a break between classes for students to complete homework assignments. Fourth and fifth grade students will log in to classes from 9:45 to 11:30 am and then from 12:15 to 1:15 pm. 4th and 5th grade teachers will be available from 1:15 to 2:30 pm for individual help if needed. K through third grades will continue on as they have. Thank you to teachers, students and parents for your cooperation. Everyone is working hard and doing their best during this trying time.

post_text:
The next week or two starts a new chapter in public education. There is a huge learning curve that students and teachers will be navigating together!!
As we embark on this thing called “eLearning,” I am asking my Facebook friends to refrain from publicly scrutinizing their children’s teachers/schools/district for the way they are teaching and/or assigning lessons.
Please offer grace to your child’s teacher and other school personnel. I promise that educating your children is still their #1 priority. ❤️
They are about to navigate uncharted waters with little, to no prep time. This is a crisis, not a time to be playing armchair quarterback. They love our kids and will be doing their absolute best!
🤍💻📝📌📎🖊📓📚🧮➗🖍➕
Please copy & paste if you are a teacher ... or want to support teachers.
And fellow educators, YOU’VE GOT THIS!
I believe in you!
-author of post unknown

Secondary students in 6 through 12 grades should log into google classroom or google meet between the hours of 9:45 and 4:05. Students will log into each class hour to complete the work for that class. Elementary students in grades K through 5 will check with their classroom teacher for assignments and directions. There are many links on the school website at www.primeroschool.org under Parent Resources for many more learning resources for students. Thank you.

post_text:
Primero school will serve lunches next week for students. The lunches will be delivered to the following sites from 12 noon to 12:30 or until everyone has been served: Cokedale bus stop for out of district students, Sarcillo fire station, Wet Canyon fire station, Picketwire and Primero school cafeteria door. Parents or guardians should bring students with them to receive the lunches so that students can be counted. Please remain in your vehicle to assure distancing and lunches will be brought to your vehicle.
Parents of K through 3 students, we would like to keep the students occupied and keep their learning as uninterrupted as possible. A daily schedule has been posted on the school website at www.primeroschool.org under Parent Resources, along with links to help keep your students engaged. If you have any trouble logging in please contact your students teacher via email or text if you have their number.
Thank you for your understanding and cooperation in this difficult situation.

post_text: Primero school will be closed after spring break until March 30. Starting March 23 classes will resume online and will follow the 2 hour delay schedule, meaning that classes will begin at 9:45 am and end at 4:05 pm. Students in grades 4 through 12 should check google classroom and google meet every day for assignments and continue working online through March 30. Students who missed school last week and were unable to get books, etc. from their classrooms or lockers may come to the school tomorrow from 9 to 11 am to retrieve those items. If you cannot come to the school at that time please call the school to make arrangements to pick up your students books and/or computers. The school building, including the community center and community fitness room are currently closed as well. Parent teacher conferences and teacher inservice has been rescheduled.

shared_text:
Joey Dunlap is with Elvis Romero.
February 13 at 7:03 AM ·

Nunca pensé que tendría un mejor amigo de Bolivia. 😁 Estoy muy agradecido por el Elder Romero y su ejemplo para mí. Ya sea que estemos comiendo flan, jugando baloncesto o dando una lección, él siempre está lleno de ánimo y lleno del Espíritu. Su deseo de servir a esta gente alimenta mi deseo, y estoy muy agradecido por eso.

Como cristianos, necesitamos tener unidad y amor por uno a otros antes que podemos compartir nuestro mensaje de Cristo con el mundo. Necesitamos pensar menos "quién es mejor" y más "a quién podemos ayudar."

Eso es lo que Jesucristo enseño 😌

Monday: Free Cooking Class begins again on March 9 from 5 to 7 pm in the school cafeteria. If your family would like to participate please call the school to register.

Tuesday, January 14: Middle school and high school boys basketball teams travel to Des Moines for games starting at 4 pm. Bus departs Primero at 1:45.

Wednesday January 15: The Primero Spelling Bee starts at 9 am. Information letters and spelling lists were sent home with students before winter break. Students should practice their spelling words to be ready for the Bee. Spectators are welcome. The Bee will begin with grades 4 through 8 in the morning and K through 3 after lunch.

Thursday, January 16: High school basketball at home against Springfield at 4 pm. Knowledge bowl meet in Pueblo.

Friday, January 17: Middle School basketball tournament starts at 9 a.m. Visiting teams are Aguilar, Des Moines and Gardner. Come out and support your Primero Bulldogs.

post_text: Summer Programming Week 1 Complete. Thank you to the dedicated staff that made it possible. We had over 10 staff (certified teachers, coaches, and admin) participate this week! We will have 3 more weeks of Summer Programming. Mon-Thurs in June from 8-12 Academics, and 12-4 Basic Skills Training. Sign ups are still accepted and this is a drop in/out style camp.

post_text: Skateland Thank you for the collaboration !! Shoutout to Ed John Ortiz You are doing great with the #Primero Youth Wrestling! Everyone is invited to the F.I.R.E. Camp next week at Skateland from 4:30-7:30 on Mon-Fri. Parents must sign registration on the spot. Spread the word to Huerfano and Las Animas Counties Early Childhood Advisory Council
shared_text:
Jaime Primmer is feeling pumped at Skateland.
June 6, 2019 at 9:13 PM · Trinidad, CO ·

This week I got to see miracles. Trinidad is full of extremely talented athletes and thanks to Primero School District doing a Free Wrestling Camp for kids I got to witness some serious fresh talent and everyone who came just had a blast💪🔥❣
